OL,3,C'Few signs' of peat recovering years
OL,4,Cafter dramatic moorland blaze
OL,6,F"There has been much recovery from
OL,7,Fplants and animals and our survey will
OL,8,Fhelp us to shape the future recovery
OL,9,Fand restoration of the complex
OL,10,Fenvironment under the ground."
OL,12,FThe ongoing surveys have found species
OL,13,Fincluding purple moor grass, turfed
OL,14,Fhair grass, wavy hair grass, mat grass
OL,15,Fand sphagnum moss, a key species known
OL,16,Fas the "sponge of the moorland" for
OL,17,Fits water-retaining properties.
OL,19,FBirds including meadow pipits,
OL,20,Fkestrels and skylarks have been
OL,21,Fspotted.
